1
00:04:19,918 --> 00:04:21,041
Pedro?

2
00:04:23,292 --> 00:04:24,334
Theo?

3
00:04:27,250 --> 00:04:28,667
Theo, how did you get in?

4
00:04:28,667 --> 00:04:30,459
Can you believe that Pedro
left me waiting...

5
00:04:30,459 --> 00:04:31,876
at the exchange student meeting?

6
00:04:33,292 --> 00:04:35,000
- What do you mean?
- He didn't show up.

7
00:04:35,209 --> 00:04:37,250
I called him up,
he didn't answer the phone.

8
00:04:37,250 --> 00:04:38,876
- He didn't show up.
- So?

9
00:04:42,459 --> 00:04:44,292
Branca, I called you up
and you didn't answer the phone.

10
00:04:44,334 --> 00:04:47,000
I've been ringing the bell for half an
hour, you didn't answer the door.

11
00:04:47,459 --> 00:04:49,417
And you left this door here open.

12
00:04:51,751 --> 00:04:53,542
Theo, there's no way.

13
00:04:53,626 --> 00:04:55,959
You can't just keep coming in
like this, without calling first.

14
00:04:56,542 --> 00:04:58,209
Branca, I'm sorry.
Is Pedro here?

15
00:05:00,000 --> 00:05:02,667
- And you can't have a key anymore.
- Branca, if our only problem...

16
00:05:02,709 --> 00:05:04,501
is me having or not having
the key to this place...

17
00:05:04,501 --> 00:05:07,918
- we were doing alright, huh?
- Yeah, that's not the problem.

18
00:05:07,959 --> 00:05:09,292
I'm the problem.

19
00:05:09,334 --> 00:05:13,250
For me to continue living here, huh?
That's the problem, right?

20
00:05:23,209 --> 00:05:25,959
I brought Zezé's money.
I want you to pay him...

21
00:05:26,000 --> 00:05:28,209
only after he finishes
waterproofing the pool.

22
00:05:28,209 --> 00:05:30,667
- Can you do that?
- Why waterproof it?

23
00:05:34,876 --> 00:05:37,209
The tiles, they'll be delivered
next week, they're already paid for.

24
00:05:37,209 --> 00:05:39,292
- Why tiles?
- Why? I don't know, Branca.

25
00:05:39,334 --> 00:05:41,375
Maybe to cover the hole
out there on the verandah.

26
00:05:41,417 --> 00:05:42,834
I don't know
why you're making a pool...

27
00:05:42,834 --> 00:05:44,375
if we're going to sell the house, Theo.

28
00:05:44,667 --> 00:05:46,834
Because it'll bring the price up,
right? Because we'll make money.

29
00:05:46,876 --> 00:05:48,876
But, maybe the guy who buys it
doesn't want a pool...

30
00:05:48,876 --> 00:05:51,083
- Yeah, he might not like the house.
- Might not know how to swim.

31
00:05:51,125 --> 00:05:53,209
Let's stop around here, please.

32
00:05:57,209 --> 00:05:59,751
I'm tired as hell. We don't even know
if we're going to sell the house.

33
00:06:01,709 --> 00:06:04,959
What do you mean?
You don't seem to understand.

34
00:06:06,000 --> 00:06:08,667
As soon as I find my own place,
I'm leaving.

35
00:06:10,667 --> 00:06:11,876
Do you understand?

36
00:06:30,250 --> 00:06:33,501
- Where were you, son?
- My computer broke.

37
00:06:33,918 --> 00:06:35,501
I took it to get fixed.

38
00:06:35,542 --> 00:06:38,083
We had an appointment today,
did you forget?

39
00:06:38,626 --> 00:06:41,626
You had. Alone.

40
00:06:44,083 --> 00:06:45,250
I had an appointment.

41
00:06:47,459 --> 00:06:48,584
Alone.

42
00:06:57,000 --> 00:06:59,250
It was important for him to go today.
Today was the day...

43
00:06:59,334 --> 00:07:01,209
They have this rule there,
that says the kids...

44
00:07:01,209 --> 00:07:03,417
have to go at least one day.
If they don't go one day...

45
00:07:04,459 --> 00:07:06,083
To be able to pick your city.

46
00:07:06,250 --> 00:07:09,000
You have to go just once.
Just one time.

47
00:07:10,959 --> 00:07:12,751
To guarantee you get Christchurch,
I had to pay.

48
00:07:12,751 --> 00:07:14,209
- Now, he'll have to go next time.
- You paid?

49
00:07:14,250 --> 00:07:15,334
You'll have to go
to the next meeting...

50
00:07:15,375 --> 00:07:17,250
Otherwise, there's no way we
can guarantee you can pick your city.

51
00:07:17,501 --> 00:07:19,751
Dad, I'm not going!
I don't want to!

52
00:07:19,792 --> 00:07:20,959
You don't...

53
00:07:23,125 --> 00:07:25,501
Why aren't you going, Pedro?
Just for me...

54
00:07:25,959 --> 00:07:28,667
The way I see it, I'm
giving him a good opportunity, right?

55
00:07:28,709 --> 00:07:30,417
Am I wrong?
Isn't it something good?

56
00:07:30,417 --> 00:07:32,250
A trip? For you to speak English,

57
00:07:32,292 --> 00:07:34,417
go to the best country
in the world.

58
00:07:34,417 --> 00:07:35,417
If I were a sheep.

59
00:07:35,459 --> 00:07:36,709
Theo, you can't force
something like this...

60
00:07:36,751 --> 00:07:39,083
But, I gave him two options.
On two different continents.

61
00:07:39,125 --> 00:07:40,626
I wish my father had
given me something like this.

62
00:07:40,667 --> 00:07:42,083
It can't always be the
way you want it.

63
00:07:42,083 --> 00:07:43,501
You thought it was
a good idea.

64
00:07:43,501 --> 00:07:44,667
And you're going to decide for him?

65
00:07:44,667 --> 00:07:47,834
- And when is he going to decide?
- When he decides, Theo. If he decides.

66
00:07:47,834 --> 00:07:50,209
You can't just send the
boy off to Australia.

67
00:08:04,334 --> 00:08:05,542
New Zealand.

68
00:08:08,083 --> 00:08:09,584
That's not the issue.

69
00:08:16,334 --> 00:08:18,167
The issue is always
something else, huh?

70
00:08:21,417 --> 00:08:22,584
Yes.

71
00:08:31,334 --> 00:08:32,876
It's always something else.

72
00:08:59,375 --> 00:09:00,751
What's that, Branca?

73
00:09:04,292 --> 00:09:05,501
What's what?

74
00:09:09,709 --> 00:09:11,834
- Theo...
- What is this chair doing here?

75
00:09:11,834 --> 00:09:14,042
It's for his birthday, Theo.

76
00:09:14,375 --> 00:09:16,959
- Why are you doing this to me?
- Nobody is doing anything.

77
00:09:17,000 --> 00:09:18,834
Why are you doing
this, man?

78
00:09:20,834 --> 00:09:23,792
Why this?
What is this, Branca?

79
00:09:23,834 --> 00:09:25,667
- Calm down, Theo.
- What is it?

80
00:09:26,792 --> 00:09:28,250
What is this chair
doing here?

81
00:09:28,250 --> 00:09:29,792
Why are you
doing this, Branca?

82
00:09:29,834 --> 00:09:32,042
- Wait, Theo, take it easy.
- Why are you doing this to me?

83
00:09:32,083 --> 00:09:34,626
- What is this chair doing here, Pedro?
- My grandfather sent it.

84
00:09:34,667 --> 00:09:36,334
Your grandfather?
But, what grandfather, Pedro?

85
00:09:36,375 --> 00:09:38,000
- Listen, Theo...
- Who is your grandfather?

86
00:09:38,042 --> 00:09:39,501
- I'm going to put it in my room.
- Wait, hold it.

87
00:09:39,501 --> 00:09:40,709
Who is your grandfather?

88
00:09:40,792 --> 00:09:41,876
- Dad...
- What grandfather?

89
00:09:41,918 --> 00:09:43,417
- I'm going to put it in my room.
- Hold it, Theo.

90
00:09:43,417 --> 00:09:44,792
Just a second, Branca.
Let me ask him.

91
00:09:44,834 --> 00:09:46,250
- Right, but don't be like this.
- Does he know his grandfather?

92
00:09:46,292 --> 00:09:47,292
Who is your grandfather?
Do you know him?

93
00:09:47,292 --> 00:09:48,918
- Give me my chair.
- Has your grandfather ever seen you?

94
00:09:48,959 --> 00:09:49,959
- Dad.
- Does he know you?

95
00:09:50,000 --> 00:09:51,292
- Let go.
- Hold it. Let me talk to you.

96
00:09:51,292 --> 00:09:52,375
- Let go of my chair.
- Does your grandfather know you?

97
00:09:52,417 --> 00:09:54,292
Hold it! Does your
grandfather know you?

98
00:09:54,334 --> 00:09:56,375
He doesn't know me!
He doesn't know you!

99
00:09:56,501 --> 00:09:58,292
- He doesn't know you!
- You don't even live here anymore!

100
00:09:58,334 --> 00:10:00,542
- Give me my chair!
- He doesn't know me!

101
00:10:00,584 --> 00:10:02,792
- He doesn't know you!
- Give me my chair!

102
00:10:02,834 --> 00:10:04,751
- Stop it, Theo!
- I'll show you all!

103
00:10:04,792 --> 00:10:06,834
- Don't do that, Theo!
- Dad!

104
00:10:08,501 --> 00:10:10,334
Do you want your key?
Do you want your key?

105
00:10:33,876 --> 00:10:39,000
FATHER'S CHAIR

106
00:10:46,667 --> 00:10:51,459
DOCTOR BRANCA GADELHA

107
00:12:43,792 --> 00:12:45,042
Pedro?

108
00:12:45,709 --> 00:12:46,959
Are you going?

109
00:12:48,417 --> 00:12:50,209
Have they come to
pick you up already?

110
00:12:50,375 --> 00:12:51,959
I'll be back on Sunday, mom.

111
00:12:53,209 --> 00:12:55,125
- Have dinner with me?
- Yes.

112
00:12:58,417 --> 00:12:59,542
Kisses.

113
00:13:00,667 --> 00:13:02,417
Happy birthday!

114
00:13:42,209 --> 00:13:44,000
I got my things.
I'm going.

115
00:13:44,042 --> 00:13:45,876
- I'll help you.
- No problem.

116
00:13:52,751 --> 00:13:53,918
I'm sorry.

117
00:13:55,459 --> 00:13:58,459
- You didn't have to do that, Theo.
- I know, I'm sorry.

118
00:13:58,918 --> 00:14:00,501
Really, you shouldn't
have done it.

119
00:14:01,584 --> 00:14:02,959
Can you forgive me?

120
00:14:05,501 --> 00:14:07,417
Did you know
about this chair?

121
00:14:08,209 --> 00:14:10,667
- Theo...
- It isn't easy for me, Branca.

122
00:14:10,709 --> 00:14:11,834
I know.

123
00:14:15,083 --> 00:14:17,542
Go back home and
I'm not living there anymore...

124
00:14:18,667 --> 00:14:19,876
it isn't easy.

125
00:14:25,834 --> 00:14:27,000
I'm sorry.

126
00:14:28,792 --> 00:14:30,125
Is Pedro up?

127
00:14:30,918 --> 00:14:32,209
Pedro went on a trip.

128
00:14:33,834 --> 00:14:36,834
- It's his birthday on Sunday.
- He went someplace with Levy.

129
00:14:37,459 --> 00:14:38,667
Did you let him go?

130
00:14:39,667 --> 00:14:41,083
He didn't ask, Theo.

131
00:14:49,125 --> 00:14:50,709
But, the exchange program,
I don't know...

132
00:14:50,751 --> 00:14:52,167
I thought it was something good.

133
00:14:52,209 --> 00:14:53,667
I thought that it was
something he'd like,

134
00:14:53,667 --> 00:14:55,501
that was good for him...

135
00:14:56,417 --> 00:14:58,834
good for him to stay
away a bit, on his own...

136
00:14:58,876 --> 00:15:00,584
while we worked things out.

137
00:15:02,209 --> 00:15:04,125
Things aren't going to
work out, Theo.

138
00:15:08,167 --> 00:15:10,209
But, he doesn't have
to stick around and watch.

139
00:15:11,751 --> 00:15:14,542
- I'm leaving that house.
- I'm not talking about that anymore.

140
00:15:14,709 --> 00:15:16,375
- I don't...
- I've already given your key back.

141
00:15:16,417 --> 00:15:17,792
- I never wanted to live in that house.
- I won't go there anymore.

142
00:15:17,792 --> 00:15:19,375
You don't want me to go?
I won't go.

143
00:15:19,375 --> 00:15:21,292
Branca, I made
that house for you.

144
00:15:21,292 --> 00:15:22,667
It was always something
you wanted, Theo.

145
00:15:22,667 --> 00:15:24,584
Let me talk.
I made that house for you.

146
00:15:24,626 --> 00:15:25,918
- Right.
- Branca.

147
00:15:26,501 --> 00:15:28,918
- Theo...
- I made the house for you, for Pedro...

148
00:15:28,918 --> 00:15:30,209
I made the house for us.

149
00:15:31,000 --> 00:15:34,042
- Stop it.
- What's happened to us? Tell me.

150
00:15:34,584 --> 00:15:37,250
- Theo, we've already talked about this.
- What's happening, Branca?

151
00:15:37,709 --> 00:15:39,417
What do you want me to do?
Tell me.

152
00:15:39,584 --> 00:15:42,250
- Theo...
- What do you want me to do?

153
00:15:42,959 --> 00:15:44,667
What do you want me to do?
Tell me?

154
00:15:48,834 --> 00:15:50,000
Tell me.

155
00:16:17,751 --> 00:16:19,751
Theo, let me go.
Theo, please.

156
00:16:19,792 --> 00:16:20,834
Theo...

157
00:16:26,751 --> 00:16:27,959
Hold it, Theo.

158
00:17:36,209 --> 00:17:38,083
- Hi.
- Hi, Theo.

159
00:17:38,834 --> 00:17:41,792
So, I'm going to have dinner
with Pedro on Sunday, at home.

160
00:17:41,834 --> 00:17:43,959
- If you want to show up.
- OK.

161
00:17:45,167 --> 00:17:46,375
I'll go.

162
00:18:02,667 --> 00:18:03,751
How's it going?

163
00:18:03,792 --> 00:18:04,834
Hi, Theo.

164
00:18:05,959 --> 00:18:07,083
Come in.

165
00:18:11,000 --> 00:18:12,501
You've already made dinner.

166
00:18:12,501 --> 00:18:14,083
No problem.

167
00:18:14,792 --> 00:18:15,959
Put it here.

168
00:18:18,918 --> 00:18:22,667
- It's just that Pedro likes...
- Yeah, he loves it.

169
00:18:22,709 --> 00:18:24,167
Do you want to
drink something?

170
00:18:25,417 --> 00:18:26,501
Water.

171
00:18:32,709 --> 00:18:33,792
Thanks.

172
00:18:34,042 --> 00:18:35,167
Sit down, Theo.

173
00:18:39,584 --> 00:18:43,167
I can't figure...

174
00:18:43,167 --> 00:18:45,083
this out...
I don't now...

175
00:18:45,125 --> 00:18:47,292
- It's here.
- No.

176
00:18:47,459 --> 00:18:49,584
There's just one cable.

177
00:19:06,083 --> 00:19:07,417
Looks good.

178
00:19:08,042 --> 00:19:10,042
Yeah, he likes these here...

179
00:19:22,334 --> 00:19:23,792
And the grant?

180
00:19:25,417 --> 00:19:27,584
- Only in September.
- Yeah right, you said before.

181
00:19:28,000 --> 00:19:29,709
Have you decided
where you're going?

182
00:19:30,375 --> 00:19:31,876
I think I prefer Spain.

183
00:19:33,375 --> 00:19:35,918
For your specialty, the
United States would be better, huh?

184
00:19:37,959 --> 00:19:40,751
It's just that in Spain, besides
medical school, there's Spain.

185
00:19:45,125 --> 00:19:46,292
Yeah.

186
00:19:50,918 --> 00:19:53,626
- Pedro's taking too long.
- Did he say what time he'd be here?

187
00:19:53,667 --> 00:19:55,876
- He didn't say.
- Didn't you tell him?

188
00:19:57,334 --> 00:19:59,709
- I just said dinner.
- Let's call?

189
00:20:00,209 --> 00:20:01,792
I've already called twice.

190
00:20:09,792 --> 00:20:11,250
I'm going to call Levy.

191
00:20:24,709 --> 00:20:26,751
Hello, Levy?

192
00:20:27,042 --> 00:20:29,918
Hi, it's Branca.
So, are you guys back already?

193
00:20:31,918 --> 00:20:33,375
What do you mean, "from where"?

194
00:20:34,792 --> 00:20:36,459
Didn't you guys travel, Levy?

195
00:20:36,751 --> 00:20:38,000
What do you mean?

196
00:20:38,501 --> 00:20:40,083
Isn't Pedro there
with you?

197
00:20:42,083 --> 00:20:43,250
Hold it, Levy.

198
00:20:43,250 --> 00:20:44,792
You don't know?
Where's Pedro?

199
00:20:45,083 --> 00:20:46,292
- Renata.
- Hi, Theo.

200
00:20:46,334 --> 00:20:48,209
- How's everything?
- Hi, Renata.

201
00:20:48,250 --> 00:20:50,042
So, Levy?
What's going on?

202
00:20:50,250 --> 00:20:53,083
Pedro told Branca that he was going
to spend the weekend with you.

203
00:20:53,125 --> 00:20:54,709
He didn't say anything to me.

204
00:20:54,751 --> 00:20:56,250
You haven't spoken to him?
He didn't call? Nothing?

205
00:20:56,292 --> 00:20:58,751
- Since Saturday.
- Didn't Pedro tell you, Levy...

206
00:20:58,751 --> 00:21:00,250
where he was going to
spend the weekend?

207
00:21:00,250 --> 00:21:02,083
- No, he didn't tell me anything.
- Tell the truth, son.

208
00:21:02,125 --> 00:21:03,167
- Levy, he said...
- I am.

209
00:21:03,167 --> 00:21:04,876
He told me he was going
to travel with you, Levy.

210
00:21:04,876 --> 00:21:06,876
No, he didn't come here.
He didn't tell me anything.

211
00:21:06,876 --> 00:21:08,292
- No way, Levy.
- Levy...

212
00:21:08,292 --> 00:21:09,584
We hardly talked this week.

213
00:21:09,584 --> 00:21:11,667
OK, no problem.
Listen...

214
00:21:12,209 --> 00:21:14,292
Do you know if he's been
hanging out with someone else?

215
00:21:14,292 --> 00:21:15,417
If he's got other friends?

216
00:21:15,417 --> 00:21:17,292
If he might be spending the night at
somebody's house that we don't know?

217
00:21:17,334 --> 00:21:20,792
- No, Theo. Nothing's changed.
- Listen, Levy, think.

218
00:21:20,834 --> 00:21:23,083
Think a bit if you remember
anything... something...

219
00:21:23,125 --> 00:21:25,751
he might have done
different, during the week.

220
00:21:25,792 --> 00:21:28,042
At school. Nothing?
You don't remember?

221
00:21:28,042 --> 00:21:31,792
- Think, son.
- I don't know, Levy, if you realize...

222
00:21:31,834 --> 00:21:35,709
just how serious this is.
Pedro disappeared.

223
00:21:35,709 --> 00:21:37,167
Do you understand?
He disappeared!

224
00:21:37,167 --> 00:21:39,334
- Branca, Branca. Levy.
- Think back, son.

225
00:21:39,375 --> 00:21:41,959
Anything you remember
might be important now.

226
00:21:42,626 --> 00:21:45,000
There is something,
he asked me for...

227
00:21:45,042 --> 00:21:47,459
he wanted the address to
my Uncle Abrão's store.

228
00:21:47,542 --> 00:21:49,334
- Who is your Uncle Abrão?
- He has a computer store.

229
00:21:49,375 --> 00:21:51,751
He wanted to sell
his computer.

230
00:21:52,542 --> 00:21:55,000
Didn't you say that he wanted
to fix his computer?

231
00:21:55,000 --> 00:21:56,417
Yeah, he wanted to get it fixed.

232
00:21:56,459 --> 00:21:57,792
No, he said he wanted to sell it.

233
00:21:57,792 --> 00:22:00,334
- What are you talking about, Levy?
- No, he wanted to fix his computer.

234
00:22:00,334 --> 00:22:03,542
- He told us that...
- He told me he wanted to sell it, Theo.

235
00:22:05,292 --> 00:22:07,042
He tried to sell
his computer to my uncle...

236
00:22:07,083 --> 00:22:08,584
but he didn't want to buy it.

237
00:22:09,042 --> 00:22:11,000
What did he want to
sell his computer for?

238
00:22:12,417 --> 00:22:14,584
He said he needed money.

239
00:22:18,125 --> 00:22:19,542
Are you sure you got
the right number?

240
00:22:19,542 --> 00:22:21,792
No, Theo. I don't know my own
son's telephone number.

241
00:22:25,209 --> 00:22:27,751
- Call home, see if he's arrived.
- I just called, Theo.

242
00:22:30,125 --> 00:22:31,918
We've got to go to
the hospitals, police stations.

243
00:22:31,959 --> 00:22:34,000
- Make a list.
